column2: so i know it has been a full week since i posted
column3: which is very unlike me. i haven't quite thought of the best way to sum up the experiences of the last week of my life into a post so this will probably be spread over a few.

column1: i was admitted into an impatient psychiatric unit
column2: as i had planned to commit suicide. the experience was both traumatic and life saving
column4: and unpredictable yet simplistic. the past week has illustrated to me how many people i have in my life that love me who would be devastated were i not around anymore. if i had to narrow down the most important lesson from this week it would be that thoughts of hopelessness and worthlessness are temporary. something terrible happening to me made me feel this way
column5: but now i know that many amazing things can happen to counteract those feelings. i am trying accept that i am still strong and resilient in spite of being brought to an all time low.

column1: i am sorry if i let any of you down. i know i have been someone many survivors have looked up to. but as i always say
column2: healing is not linear. i want you all to see me throughout the many moments of profound empowerment and sadness
column3: because that is the reality of coping with trauma. i love you all.

column1: 117067;instagram;2018-12-11 16:04:38;TRUE;;"can we talk about activism for a moment?
i often find myself conflicted in what oppression i must use my voice to fight for each day: my womanhood or blackness. while my reproductive rights are being imposed on
column2: the black child i could one day birth is at risk of being killed with no justice for his skin color alone. i am often exhausted when i'm reading through books on women's history knowing that as a black woman my ancestors were surviving the trauma of slavery or jim crow and not given the option of the same ambition.

column1: as i use my voice to advocate for the things that matter to me it is essential that both parts of my existence
column3: are wholly and fully considered. i am a woman
column4: i am black and to be both is to be in a continuous state of conflicting anger and frustration in a country that has built itself on my oppression.

column1: as i am learning and growing and finding my voice as someone taking up space as an activist
column2: i ask that you be aware that i am pushing through barriers that are sticky & uncomfortable & complicated and i am trying my best. i am fighting for my black body
column3: i am fighting for my humanity as a woman
column4: i am reading and writing in search of answers that will lead to actions that will lead to some sort of sanity.

column1: i'm grateful for all the black women who are mentoring me on how to be a black woman fighting. i'm thankful to all the people who don't look like me who are listening and learning from what i've experienced and studied. i'm grateful to have a space and a voice to be heard.
studying anthropology at @columbia is one of my answers: becoming as knowledgeable as possible about history and humanity so that i can speak and teach from a space of facts
column2: education and truth whenever needed. my therapy fund for black women and girls is one of my answers: a commitment to developing tangible action based options behind my platform. likes and comments don‚Äôt translate into reparations
column3: we had to take that step further. i have more developments on the horizon that align with this work i do. i pray your continued support.

column1: i was 15 years old. i was spending the night at a ""friend's"" house. we had been drinking and my on again off again boyfriend came over with his friend. i remember going in the bedroom with my boyfriend. it was dark. i remember him being on top of me. my mind was hazy from drinking. i remember grabbing his head and realizing his hair felt different. i called his name and he answered
column2: but his voice sounded distant. it felt like another set of hands were touching me. i heard a laugh. my memory ends there. i woke up the next morning and something didn't feel right. i knew something had happened to me
column3: but i was almost afraid to know. i asked him if someone else was in the room that night and he laughed and made a joke. i asked again
column4: but this time i asked if his friend was in the room and explained that i grabbed for his hair and it felt different. he laughed again and said no. i didn't believe him. i felt stupid
column6: and embarrassed. i blamed myself because i had been drinking. i couldn't prove anything and i was too ashamed to talk to my so called friend about it. i also didn't want to run the risk of it getting out and being labeled a slut
column7: so i did my best to forget about it. that fuzzy memory has haunted me for years. i now know that an intoxicated person can't consent and everything that happened to me in that room that night was a violation. i just wish i could remember it all..... #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate";;en;#childsexabuseawareness

have you ever had a crazy idea? something that kept you up at night and gave you goosebumps when you thought about it? many of us do
column3: these are the magical parts of life - the scary
column5: beautiful things that make this short ride so wild and wonderful.

column1: i haven't been posting much lately on social media.
i went through some really difficult times (many of you read my #metoo post) and thanks to discovering how love should be through working with @apexprotectionproject
column2: i once again stepped back into my own skin.

column1: then i went away for a while
column2: discovered a place away from the world that further rejuvenated who i truly am.
i am forever grateful. they showed me what home feels like and gave me a part of the world to call my own.

column1: now it's time to start a new chapter
column2: and set off on a journey to bring a truly mad idea into being.
and i have so many amazing people in my life who prove that our species can do the most beautiful

column1: i want to not just believe in a better tomorrow
column2: i want to try and help to create it. for me
column3: the point is to try and leave this beautiful world a little better than you found it.

column1: so i am excited to introduce you to the next chapter of my life
column2: and a project that i hope will make an impact.

column1: i still whole heartedly support #metoo despite my experiences  it is already tremendously successful  and i believe its time for all men to support the rise of the divine feminine especially in cultural and governmental affairs. we need more nurturing and thoughtful leadership  in these powerful positions... hollywood is where social justice and other issues travel  so it makes sense that they should lead it  and i applaud the women doing the work. as for me i have been a playboy all my life i accept that the new more accurate term for playboy is womanizer  therefore i accept that i have been part of the problem  and i‚Äôm here now to be part of the solution  hollywood is a great place to brand an idea and it has been tremendously helpful in pointing out where we as a society need lots of work  however hollywood is also the place where money and fame are sought after the most ... in every great revolution there is some collateral damage  i am sad  for the many men who are being extorted or unjustly accused (and there are many)  but  it is worth it if my daughters will live in a world where the agenda for women is advanced  i am fearful left that without a shift to balance this current wave of unconscious masculine leadership
column2: we as a species could be fucked... the future must be more brown

column2: what kind of society justifies mass murder and unnecessary killing? you must stop saying that animals aren't victims just because we aren't human. think about it. the victimizer's mindset always goes like this: you don't count because you're stupid. you don't matter because you're dumb. i am better than you and i laugh at your suffering. i kill you when i want to. i sell you and your family. you're worthless. you don't think the way i do.

prove to me that your life is more valuable than mine. prove to me why i should be kind to you. prove to me that you deserve to be free. prove to me that you deserve to be respected. prove to me that you are respecting life. prove to me that you know what justice is.

column1: 117445;instagram;2018-12-11 09:37:47;FALSE;"ah so lovely to step back (or escape) into the #glamourous expensive world with #emily
column2: where she is now an image consultant who is a little bit down on her luck. a mutual acquaintance needs her help and emily and two other strong female leads all work together to exact revenge. they even come up triumph against their own personal battles they face day to day alongside the main crisis they are dealing with.

column1: i loved this book and read it in two sittings
column2: just could not put this down. i also love how #lauren references recent events in the celebrity world including #metoo so the book is very topical and relevant. oh and did i also mention that #miranda priestly also features? .

column1: the prefect book to read on holiday
column5: just anywhere. a must read and you won't be disappointed.

column4: pure escapism. loved it. best book i've read in a long time..

117540;instagram;2018-12-11 07:13:01;FALSE;"i see healing from trauma in three stages:
this belongs to those who are currently in a traumatic/abusive/unsafe situation or relationship
this category includes people who are not actively living in a traumatic situation but are dealing with the aftermath of their trauma.
this final category are those who have worked through the trauma enough and can embrace the here and now while anticipating the future.
to move from one stage to the next is a conscious choice.  at some point
column2: a victim of domestic violence has to make the choice to leave the relationship.

a survivor has to choose to do the deep-level work of facing and dealing with their traumas to live mindfully and wholeheartedly each day. ******************************************* back in may 2017 when i had my breakdown
column3: i left the mental hospital determined to slay the dragons that kept me from moving ahead in my life.

column1: i was tired of simply surviving my past.  i am a sexual abuse

column2: i'd been doing a lot of work through therapy since 2011 but i was still missing a huge piece of the puzzle for healing myself.

column1: i made a choice to reprogram my own ""i hate me"" message which i have literally carved into my own arm and learn ""i love myself"" thoughts and actions.  i remember thinking to myself
column2: ""i am soooo sick of just surviving my past.  i want to learn to thrive.  i have only one life and i want it to be the best it could ever be."" this has required daily practice and mindfulness on my part.  below in the comments is my current lifestyle practice i use to teach myself self-love and self-care.

column2: leave this life and go be a mom! she just cried! it broke my heart because i also know the pain of what it feels like to not be able to just ‚Äúgo home!‚Äù the man that owned the apartment got on to me about putting crazy ideas in his girls head.

column1: at the time i didn‚Äôt know what that meant. years later i now know that he was their pimp. someone i personally knew was selling these girls and keeping them high to fill his pocket book.  i will never forget the look in her eyes and the pain she felt. i also wish there was more that i could have done but i to was sick.

column3: stand up for what is right! even if your scared! i wish i could have used my voice that night and i pray for those women who feel that there is no way out.

column2: kelompok perempuan dan gerakan perempuan menjadi motor penggerak utama bagi upaya mendesakkan ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual dan karenanya ruu ini mudah disalahpahami sebagai semata kepentingan perempuan bahkan disalahpahami sebagai kepentingan perempuan pembenci laki-laki. konsekuensinya laki-laki merasa tidak memiliki kepentingan atas ruu ini bahkan mungkin dianggap sebagai bentuk ancaman terhadap privilese (perlakuan istimewa) yang mereka nikmati selama ini yang meletakkan laki-laki sebagai subyek seksual dan memiliki hak untuk mendapatkan layanan seksual baik dalam situasi ada atau tidak ada kerelaan dari perempuan.

column2: rancangan undang-undang ini dapat menjadi istrumen bagi mayoritas laki-laki bukan pelaku kekerasan seksual untuk keluar dari stigma atau cap negatif yang harus mereka tanggung sebagai akibat dari perilaku segelintir laki-laki pelaku kekerasan seksual. cap negatif terhadap laki-laki selalu muncul pada saat kasus kekerasan seksual muncul ke publik. laki-laki harus rela dicap otaknya ngeres
column4: tak dapat mengendalikan hasrat seksual dan sederet cap negatif lainnya. dengan terlibat dalam upaya mendesak ruu pks

column7: dan menginginkan relasi seksual konsensual yang menyenangkan dan tidak menyakiti serta menolak segala bentuk kekerasan seksual baik di ranah privat maupun publik.

column1: 117891;instagram;2018-12-10 23:01:18;FALSE;"i have so much to say in this post.... thank you all for reaching out to me not just today and yesterday but for months now.... complementing my strength for coming forward and making our documentary. i want everyone to know as horrible as the things that have happened to myself and many others. i have no pain there anymore... i'm ok
column3: hurt and fear i once felt has turned into power and strength. it has pushed me to become stronger than i ever thought i could possibly be. horrible experiences can break us or build us. i choose to let it build me up. make me more confident and powerful. i'm in no way perfect. i believe the reason i'm so emotionally detached from ever wanting a real relationship with a man is a result of it. i can be very cold and emotionless and have a hard time letting anyone in. so i can't say i left completely unbroken. but i have learned to be happy in life i need to love me. love me more than any man or woman ever could and i do. it took a while to get there. but i know no matter what i'm ok because i have myself and i'm enough. i have my amazing kids who love me more than life itself and a career that means everything to me. for the ladies that have reached out to me just know it's a journey but you'll get there as well and i'm here for you always live your fully with no regrets!!!! take chances do what makes you happy! üíô #metoo #metoomovement

column1: 117907;instagram;2018-12-10 23:11:20;FALSE;"it's been a rough couple days with ptsd being pretty activated; causing mood swings
column3: depression and heightened eating disorder urges.

column1: i spent most of yesterday sleeping which resulted in me feeling pretty low about myself by the time evening came around. so i asked a friend to come over and talk with me for awhile. it was helpful to have a friend there to listen to me and validate my emotions.
today i decided i didn't like the way i felt last evening
column2: so although it was hard to get out of bed
column4: and made a to do list and a schedule for the day. i started out being fairly productive
column7: changing my sheets etc. but those feelings of dread and fear and the unyielding need crept in. so i decided it was time to stop focusing on just doing things
column8: and start focusing on doing things for myself. i was feeling vulnerable
column9: scared and alone and i was in need of some self care. so thats exactly what i did. i went to the mall and got myself some bubble tea
column10: bought a mud mask for when i get home tonight and then treated myself to a movie date with myself üòò

column2: i have not done everything i needed to do in terms of my meal plan today
